  "prompt": "What are the benefits of becoming a partner in a PE firm vs. a consulting company (McKinsey, BCG, Bain)?",
  "response": "Let me break down the key differences and comparative benefits:\n\nPrivate Equity Partner:\nPros:\n- Much higher compensation potential ($1-5M+ annually)\n- Direct equity ownership/upside\n- More entrepreneurial environment\n- Strong financial incentives tied to investment performance\n- Less travel compared to consulting\n- More direct control over business strategy\n\nConsulting Partner:\nPros:\n- More stable/predictable income\n- Broader industry exposure\n- Lower personal financial risk\n- Prestigious brand/network\n- More intellectual diversity in work\n- Better work-life balance\n- Clear career progression path\n\nPE Partnership Considerations:\n- Higher financial risk\n- Performance directly tied to investment returns\n- More complex compensation structure\n- Requires strong investment/deal-making skills\n- Often need prior PE/investment banking experience\n\nConsulting Partnership Considerations:\n- More dependent on client relationship/rainmaking\n- Requires strong client development skills\n- More structured advancement process\n- Broader strategic skill set required\n\nFinancial Comparison:\nPE Partner: $1-5M+ (highly variable)\nTop Consulting Partner: $500K-$1.5M\n\nUltimately depends on:\n- Personal risk tolerance\n- Financial goals\n- Professional interests\n- Skill set alignment\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of this comparison?",
